# webserv-tester

*This project has been created as part of the 42 curriculum.*

An HTTP tester for the **Webserv** project. It auto-generates the required file infrastructure and configuration, then runs 100+ tests covering everything the subject requires: static files, upload, redirection, directory listing, CGI, error pages, body limits, chunked encoding, HTTP smuggling, slowloris, and more.

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.6+
- No external dependencies вҖ” stdlib only

---

## Quickstart

```bash
# 1. Clone
git clone https://github.com/<you>/webserv-tester
cd webserv-tester

# 2. Generate the file infrastructure and tester.conf
python3 tester.py init

# 3. Start your server with the generated config
./webserv tester.conf

# 4. Run the tests
python3 tester.py run
```

---

## Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `python3 tester.py init` | Creates `www/`, `logs/`, all HTML files, and `tester.conf` |
| `python3 tester.py run` | Runs all tests (checks infra + server first) |
| `python3 tester.py check` | Shows infra and server status without running tests |
| `python3 tester.py clean` | Deletes all generated files (fresh start) |
| `python3 tester.py help` | Displays usage and current config |

### Options

```bash
python3 tester.py run   --host 127.0.0.1  # default
python3 tester.py run   --port 8080        # default
python3 tester.py init  --host 127.0.2.1 --port 9090
```

`--host` and `--port` affect both the generated `tester.conf` and the requests sent during tests.

---

## What gets generated

Running `init` creates this structure next to `tester.py`:

```
webserv-tester/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ tester.py
в”ңв”Җв”Җ tester.conf          вҶҗ ready to pass to ./webserv
в”ңв”Җв”Җ www/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ index.html
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ contact.html
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ uploads/         вҶҗ upload destination
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ files/           вҶҗ directory listing (autoindex on)
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ sample.txt
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ cgi-bin/
в”Ӯ   в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ hello.py     вҶҗ CGI test script (chmod 755)
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ errors/
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 400.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 403.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 404.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 405.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 413.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 431.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 500.html
в”Ӯ       в”ңв”Җв”Җ 505.html
в”Ӯ       в””в”Җв”Җ error.html
в””в”Җв”Җ logs/
    в”ңв”Җв”Җ access.log
    в””в”Җв”Җ error.log
```

---

## Configuration overview

The generated `tester.conf` defines two virtual hosts on the same port:

**localhost** вҖ” main vhost
| Route | Methods | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| `/` | GET | static root |
| `/contacts` | GET POST DELETE | `client_max_body_size 1MB` |
| `/upload` | POST | stores files in `www/uploads/` |
| `/upload/delete` | DELETE | deletes uploaded files |
| `/files` | GET | `autoindex on` вҖ” directory listing |
| `/old` | вҖ” | `301 вҶ’  /` |
| `/temp` | вҖ” | `302 вҶ’ /contacts` |
| `/cgi-bin` | GET POST | `.py` executed with `python3` |

**secondary** вҖ” restricted vhost (`client_max_body_size 0`)
| Route | Methods |
|---|---|
| `/upload` | POST (`client_max_body_size 1MB` override) |
| `/delete` | DELETE |

---

## Test coverage

| Section | # tests | Subject requirement |
|---|---|---|
| Valid requests | 10 | GET / POST / DELETE |
| Upload | 5 | *"clients must be able to upload files"* |
| Redirection | 2 | *"HTTP redirection"* |
| Directory listing | 3 | *"enabling/disabling directory listing"* |
| CGI | 3 | *"execution of CGI based on file extension"* |
| Methods | 14 | allowed / forbidden / malformed |
| Headers | 20 | malformed, missing, injected, too long |
| Body | 15 | size limits, chunked, Content-Length edge cases |
| URI | 14 | traversal, encoding, null bytes, length |
| Protocol | 7 | HTTP version handling |
| Request line format | 7 | CRLF, spacing, tabs |
| Static files | 3 | *"serve a fully static website"* |
| Error pages | 3 | *"must have default error pages"* |
| Response headers | 3 | Content-Type, Content-Length presence |
| HTTP Smuggling | 3 | CL-TE, TE obfuscation, chunk overflow |
| Pipelining | 2 | multiple requests on one connection |
| Slowloris / DoS | 2 | *"server must remain available at all times"* |
| Unicode / Encoding | 2 | overlong UTF-8, double percent-encoding |

**Total: 118 tests**

---

## Output format

```
  [PASS]  VALID_GET                                     HTTP/1.1 200 OK  (1.2 ms)
  [FAIL]  CHUNKED_VALID                                 got [HTTP/1.1 500 ...]  expected 200|201
  [ERR ]  BODY_TOO_BIG                                  [Errno 104] Connection reset  (expected 413)
```

A progress bar summarises results at the end:

```
  в–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–Ҳв–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘в–‘  98 passed / 4 failed / 1 errors / 103 total
```

---

## Behaviour without arguments

Running `python3 tester.py` with no arguments behaves automatically:
- If the infrastructure doesn't exist yet вҶ’ runs `init`
- If it exists but the server isn't up вҶ’ prints the launch command and exits
- If it exists and the server is up вҶ’ runs all tests

---

## Notes

- The CGI test requires `python3` at `/usr/bin/python3`. Adjust `cgi_extension` in `tester.conf` if your path differs.
- `clean` removes `www/`, `logs/`, and `tester.conf`. Your `tester.py` is never touched.
- Tests marked `(200|201)` or `(200|404)` accept multiple valid codes вҖ” implementations may differ on details the subject leaves open.
- The subject says *"a request to your server should never hang indefinitely"* вҖ” the slowloris tests verify exactly this.